FLUID-SOLID 2D HYDROSTATIC TEST
-------------------------------
Inviscid fluid at rest in a [-5,5]^2 solid-containing domain subject to
gravity; solid/fluid are side-by-side. Fluid should remain at rest, with
a linear pressure field.

With g=(1,0,0): rho = 2, p = c + x, in x > 0

Variations use rotated meshes (and rotated g)

&OUTPUTS
  output_t  = 0.0, 2.0
  output_dt = 2.0
/

&MESH
  mesh_file = 'mesh1.gen'
/

&PHYSICS
  flow = .true.
  body_force_density = 1.0, 0.0, 0.0
/

&FLOW
  inviscid = .true.
  courant_number = 0.5
/

&FLOW_CORRECTOR
  rel_tol = 0.0
  abs_tol = 1.0e-12
  max_ds_iter = 50
  max_amg_iter = 25
  krylov_method = 'cg'
/

&NUMERICS
  dt_constant = 0.125
/

# FREE SLIP BC ALL AROUND
&FLOW_BC
  name = 'all sides'
  face_set_ids = 1, 2, 3, 4, 5
  condition = 'slip'
/

Lower half
&BODY
  surface_name = 'from mesh file'
  mesh_material_number = 1
  material_number = 2
  temperature = 0.0
/

upper half
&BODY
  surface_name = 'from mesh file'
  mesh_material_number = 2
  material_number = 1
  velocity = 3*0.0
  temperature = 0.0
/

&MATERIAL
  material_name    = 'water'
  material_number  = 1
  density          = 1.0  ! not void
  material_feature = 'background'
/

&PHASE
  name = 'water'
  property_name(1) = 'density',       property_constant(1) = 2.0
  property_name(2) = 'specific heat', property_constant(2) = 1.0
/

&MATERIAL_SYSTEM
  name = 'water'
  phases = 'water'
/

&MATERIAL
  material_name    = 'solid'
  material_number  = 2
  density          = 1.0  ! not void
  immobile         = .true.
/

&PHASE
  name = 'solid'
  property_name(1) = 'density',       property_constant(1) = 1.0
  property_name(2) = 'specific heat', property_constant(2) = 1.0
/

&MATERIAL_SYSTEM
  name = 'solid'
  phases = 'solid'
/
